==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embankment
<hw>Em*bank"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of surrounding or defending with a bank.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A structure of earth, gravel, etc., raised to
prevent water from overflowing a level tract of country, to retain water
in a reservoir, or to carry a roadway, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embar</ent>⟦br⟧
